In particular, the name of Spain's capital, Madrid, has been linked to the euro on at least two important occasions: the Madrid European Council of July 1989 adopted the Delors plan on Economic and Monetary Union; 
  and
 the Madrid European Council of 15 December 1995 saw the establishment of this new European currency.

This path does not mean we need not concentrate on the political and social dimension of European integration; 

            on the contrary

        , that is what it requires.
